The paper deals with geometric graphs and spanners, which are topics commonly studied in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The results also involve combinatorial and algorithmic aspects, which could fall under discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the maximum degree of hop spanners, which could be relevant to the study of network algorithms (cs.SI).
